1
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:35,009
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,470 --> 00:01:37,920
[Episode 1]

3
00:01:38,810 --> 00:01:41,600
[1994, Yantai, Shandong]

4
00:01:44,620 --> 00:01:45,350
Come on, come on!

5
00:01:45,350 --> 00:01:45,780
Here.

6
00:01:47,420 --> 00:01:47,950
Weigh it!

7
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:50,500
Load this crate onto Truck One.

8
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:51,100
Truck One.

9
00:01:53,570 --> 00:01:54,620
A bad one.

10
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:01,370
Weigh it!

11
00:02:14,650 --> 00:02:15,180
Shengli,

12
00:02:15,620 --> 00:02:17,300
any news on that script of yours?

13
00:02:17,300 --> 00:02:18,700
I'll hear back very soon!

14
00:02:21,430 --> 00:02:23,630
If you want something different...

15
00:02:26,340 --> 00:02:27,480
If you want something different...

16
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:31,670
[Jinhai Seafood Processing Plant]

17
00:02:41,780 --> 00:02:42,710
Unload the fish!

18
00:02:45,620 --> 00:02:46,150
Let's go.

19
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:48,190
Feng!

20
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:49,410
Feng!

21
00:02:50,650 --> 00:02:51,240
Shengli!

22
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:52,910
Back from the supply run?

23
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:54,410
[Porter's Lodge]

24
00:02:53,430 --> 00:02:54,520
L-Let's go for lunch.

25
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,720
Any mail for me today?

26
00:02:55,880 --> 00:03:02,090
[Porter's Lodge]

27
00:02:58,020 --> 00:02:59,710
Well... early this morning,

28
00:03:00,470 --> 00:03:01,800
Director Wang took your letter

29
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:02,430
again.

30
00:03:03,590 --> 00:03:05,320
He still hasn't given it to you?

31
00:03:07,530 --> 00:03:08,430
No, S-Shengli!

32
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:09,900
Don't tell him I told you!

33
00:03:13,510 --> 00:03:17,350
[Certificate]

34
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,090
Xu Shengli's handwriting

35
00:03:16,470 --> 00:03:17,870
is actually pretty good.

36
00:03:18,020 --> 00:03:18,400
Liu.

37
00:03:18,460 --> 00:03:20,190
What's the use?

38
00:03:20,190 --> 00:03:22,240
-Did he even write it himself?
-Drinking at noon?

39
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:24,970
-What if someone sees it?
-There's no one around.

40
00:03:25,150 --> 00:03:25,910
You don't get flushed anyway.

41
00:03:25,910 --> 00:03:26,690
I know that.

42
00:03:26,810 --> 00:03:27,140
Here.

43
00:03:27,930 --> 00:03:28,930
Here, let me do it.

44
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:31,190
It's okay. It's okay.

45
00:03:31,190 --> 00:03:31,560
I'll get it.

46
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:32,220
I'll wipe it.

47
00:03:32,220 --> 00:03:33,150
Wipe it.

48
00:03:38,970 --> 00:03:40,030
Director, where is my letter?

49
00:03:40,030 --> 00:03:40,760
What letter?

50
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:42,680
It's lunch break!

51
00:03:43,060 --> 00:03:44,520
Come back this afternoon!

52
00:03:50,130 --> 00:03:51,260
These aren't yours!

53
00:03:51,810 --> 00:03:52,710
What are you doing?

54
00:03:52,710 --> 00:03:53,510
Aren't you...

55
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:54,960
Xu Shengli!

56
00:03:56,079 --> 00:03:56,650
Get off!

57
00:03:58,210 --> 00:03:59,800
What are you doing?

58
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:00,620
Xu Shengli!

59
00:04:02,810 --> 00:04:03,590
What are you doing?

60
00:04:03,590 --> 00:04:06,280
Who gave you the right
to take my registered mail?

61
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,660
Film studio?

62
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:10,480
A film studio is still another company!

63
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:12,150
A couple of lousy skits

64
00:04:12,150 --> 00:04:13,240
and some crappy awards

65
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:14,530
don't make you somebody!

66
00:04:14,530 --> 00:04:15,240
Listen up,

67
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:17,690
you're just an ordinary worker

68
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:19,060
at the seafood processing plant!

69
00:04:19,060 --> 00:04:20,769
You're just like your mom—

70
00:04:21,010 --> 00:04:22,190
always overreaching!

71
00:04:22,190 --> 00:04:23,010
Back then, she had to
take the college entrance exam—

72
00:04:23,010 --> 00:04:24,220
but did she get in?

73
00:04:24,390 --> 00:04:25,630
She ended up back here
grilling fish anyway!

74
00:04:25,630 --> 00:04:26,690
It's her fate.

75
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:27,860
It's your fate too!

76
00:04:27,930 --> 00:04:29,390
Your whole family's fate!

77
00:04:30,660 --> 00:04:31,990
What are you staring at?

78
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:33,620
This is your stuff, isn't it?

79
00:04:33,620 --> 00:04:34,190
Take it!

80
00:04:35,159 --> 00:04:36,040
If you want to work, work!

81
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,010
If not, get lost!

82
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:40,740
[Outstanding
Environmental Compliance Enterprise]

83
00:04:47,690 --> 00:04:48,220
Get lost!

84
00:04:56,860 --> 00:04:57,930
What are you all looking at?

85
00:04:57,930 --> 00:04:58,860
Get back to work!

86
00:04:59,810 --> 00:05:00,670
Close the door.

87
00:05:03,130 --> 00:05:03,540
Liu.

88
00:05:03,810 --> 00:05:04,450
Director.

89
00:05:04,450 --> 00:05:05,050
It's okay.

90
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,450
I'm here. What are you afraid of?

91
00:05:07,450 --> 00:05:08,740
I was so scared.

92
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,330
My heart...

93
00:05:10,430 --> 00:05:11,680
-is still pounding hard.
-Did he hurt you?

94
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:12,300
No.

95
00:05:12,510 --> 00:05:13,100
What about you?

96
00:05:13,100 --> 00:05:14,100
Are you all right?

97
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:15,220
He would never dare do something to me.

98
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:17,620
A brat like that
needs to be put in his place!

99
00:05:19,430 --> 00:05:20,300
Shengli, Shengli!

100
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:22,560
Let's talk this out! Don't be impulsive!

101
00:05:26,910 --> 00:05:28,260
[Technical Department]
[Quality Inspection Department]

102
00:05:28,260 --> 00:05:31,460
[Finance Department]
[Personnel Department]

103
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:29,800
Security!

104
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:30,450
Help!

105
00:05:30,450 --> 00:05:31,070
Shengli!

106
00:05:32,070 --> 00:05:32,960
Put that down!

107
00:05:37,159 --> 00:05:38,159
Stop right there!

108
00:05:39,250 --> 00:05:40,560
Don't run! Stop!

109
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:43,430
Stop right there! Don't run!

110
00:05:50,930 --> 00:05:51,620
Son,

111
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:54,159
I got you some ice. Here.

112
00:05:56,540 --> 00:05:58,050
Put it on yourself first.

113
00:05:59,450 --> 00:06:01,040
Are you hurt anywhere else?

114
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,760
Let's go to the hospital.

115
00:06:02,930 --> 00:06:04,370
No need. I'm really fine.

116
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:06,350
It's okay.

117
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:09,080
We've already paid the compensation.

118
00:06:09,180 --> 00:06:10,690
Later, I'll take you

119
00:06:10,690 --> 00:06:12,660
to see Director Wang
and the factory leaders—

120
00:06:12,660 --> 00:06:14,010
we'll apologize properly,

121
00:06:14,010 --> 00:06:15,930
and this whole thing will blow over.

122
00:06:15,930 --> 00:06:17,330
Mom, I did nothing wrong.

123
00:06:17,430 --> 00:06:18,570
Why should I apologize?

124
00:06:18,570 --> 00:06:20,770
I've long wanted to quit this lousy job!

125
00:06:21,330 --> 00:06:22,130
"Lousy job?"

126
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:23,570
Your mom and I

127
00:06:23,570 --> 00:06:24,430
begged everyone we knew

128
00:06:24,430 --> 00:06:25,830
to get you this lousy job,

129
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:26,920
letting you take over your mom's position

130
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:27,650
at the plant!

131
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:30,230
It's a state-owned factory.

132
00:06:30,570 --> 00:06:32,700
So many people are dying to work there!

133
00:06:32,810 --> 00:06:33,810
And what do you do?

134
00:06:34,010 --> 00:06:35,240
Not only do you not appreciate it,

135
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:36,190
but you spend all day,

136
00:06:36,190 --> 00:06:37,630
every day, on that crappy script of yours!

137
00:06:37,630 --> 00:06:38,620
Why bother even writing it?

138
00:06:38,620 --> 00:06:39,930
Does anyone actually read it?

139
00:06:39,930 --> 00:06:41,530
You don't understand at all!

140
00:06:41,540 --> 00:06:42,720
I put my heart and soul into it!

141
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:43,580
Heart and soul?

142
00:06:44,250 --> 00:06:45,300
Once you're fired

143
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,220
and starving,

144
00:06:46,659 --> 00:06:48,190
you won't have either left!

145
00:06:48,220 --> 00:06:48,890
I don't care!

146
00:06:48,890 --> 00:06:49,720
I don't want to keep

147
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:50,620
flipping those fish

148
00:06:50,620 --> 00:06:51,510
for the rest of my life!

149
00:06:51,510 --> 00:06:52,240
Flipping...

150
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:53,300
What's wrong with flipping fish?

151
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:54,330
If you don't...
If you don't want to do it,

152
00:06:54,330 --> 00:06:55,300
what do you want to do?

153
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:55,890
Tell me!

154
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:57,170
Get out of my way!

155
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:59,220
What's wrong with flipping fish?

156
00:06:59,330 --> 00:06:59,870
If you don't flip fish

157
00:06:59,870 --> 00:07:00,980
but rely on...

158
00:07:01,100 --> 00:07:02,230
w-writing scripts,

159
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:03,540
can you even make a living off it?

160
00:07:03,540 --> 00:07:04,800
How do you know I can't?

161
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:06,480
I can support myself

162
00:07:06,830 --> 00:07:08,440
and give you a better life!

163
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:09,120
You...

164
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:10,470
Give us... Bah!

165
00:07:11,810 --> 00:07:13,560
W-We're living just fine!

166
00:07:13,630 --> 00:07:15,040
We don't need you to worry!

167
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:15,570
You,

168
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:17,330
just sort yourself out!

169
00:07:17,390 --> 00:07:18,510
If you make us worry less,

170
00:07:18,510 --> 00:07:20,310
we'll be thanking God, you know?

171
00:07:20,390 --> 00:07:22,190
-Alright, that's enough.
-Always chasing pipe dreams.

172
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:23,360
Keep talking about writing scripts,

173
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:24,620
but have you actually written anything
that worked?

174
00:07:24,620 --> 00:07:25,930
You just don't have what it takes!

175
00:07:25,930 --> 00:07:27,300
How many times
have your drafts been sent back?

176
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:28,130
If you hadn't

177
00:07:28,130 --> 00:07:29,560
neglected your work for writing scripts,

178
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:31,420
would your superior have criticized you?

179
00:07:31,420 --> 00:07:32,150
And you hit him!

180
00:07:32,150 --> 00:07:33,950
What right do you have to hit him?

181
00:07:34,060 --> 00:07:36,720
You don't know anything,
yet you're blaming me.

182
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:37,920
I've decided!

183
00:07:38,450 --> 00:07:39,650
I'm going to Beijing!

184
00:07:40,070 --> 00:07:40,890
Where are you going?

185
00:07:40,890 --> 00:07:41,430
Where?

186
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:42,300
To Beijing!

187
00:07:42,430 --> 00:07:43,930
Do you know what kind of place Beijing is?

188
00:07:43,930 --> 00:07:45,220
What are you going to do there?

189
00:07:45,220 --> 00:07:46,270
Anything—whatever it takes!

190
00:07:46,270 --> 00:07:46,670
You...

191
00:07:46,810 --> 00:07:48,450
You'll starve to death there!

192
00:07:48,450 --> 00:07:49,370
You'll end up begging!

193
00:07:49,370 --> 00:07:50,800
Even if I end up begging on the streets,
that's got nothing to do with you!

194
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,070
Say that again?

195
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:55,130
Say it!

196
00:08:41,289 --> 00:08:42,690
Mom, I think I can make it.

197
00:08:44,820 --> 00:08:45,750
I believe in you.

198
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:47,730
You can definitely make it.

199
00:08:51,740 --> 00:08:52,030
Mom,

200
00:08:52,030 --> 00:08:53,700
I really love writing.

201
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:56,900
And I really want to
give it a shot in Beijing!

202
00:08:57,130 --> 00:08:58,620
I'll check for tickets tomorrow.

203
00:08:58,620 --> 00:08:59,550
Don't tell Dad.

204
00:09:10,650 --> 00:09:11,240
Son...

205
00:09:12,870 --> 00:09:14,130
Since you've decided,

206
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:15,290
give it your all.

207
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,760
We raised you all these years.

208
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:26,860
Just don't leave

209
00:09:27,770 --> 00:09:29,340
without saying goodbye.

210
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:33,000
You go check for tickets tomorrow.

211
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,340
I'll help you pack.

212
00:09:44,620 --> 00:09:45,280
Go to sleep.

213
00:09:45,870 --> 00:09:46,530
Go to sleep.

214
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:07,060
[Mr. Xu Shengli,
Your essay "Happy New Year"]

215
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:08,240
[has been selected as one of Yantai's
Top Ten Outstanding Essays.]

216
00:10:08,260 --> 00:10:09,450
[This certificate is awarded
in recognition of this achievement.]

217
00:10:09,470 --> 00:10:10,610
[Mr. Xu Shengli,
Your essay "Stories of a Small Town"]

218
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:12,120
[has been selected as one of Yantai's
Top Ten Outstanding Essays.]

219
00:10:12,140 --> 00:10:13,910
[This certificate is awarded
in recognition of this achievement.]

220
00:10:14,050 --> 00:10:17,460
[Maritime Scouts]

221
00:10:17,460 --> 00:10:19,380
[A Gathering of Heroes]

222
00:10:31,340 --> 00:10:35,410
[Yantai Station]

223
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:35,100
I'm fine.

224
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:36,600
Is the bag too heavy?

225
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:37,650
No.

226
00:10:37,650 --> 00:10:38,850
It's not heavy at all!

227
00:10:39,980 --> 00:10:41,250
Don't blame your dad.

228
00:10:41,460 --> 00:10:42,000
Last night,

229
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:44,410
he spent the whole night
packing these bags.

230
00:10:44,410 --> 00:10:45,790
I asked him to come with me
to the station,

231
00:10:45,790 --> 00:10:47,520
but he refused, no matter what—

232
00:10:49,110 --> 00:10:50,110
stubborn as ever.

233
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:52,650
And you're a chip off the old block.

234
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:54,730
Actually, I know.

235
00:10:56,150 --> 00:10:57,610
Tell Dad when you get back—

236
00:10:58,650 --> 00:11:00,010
I'll definitely make something

237
00:11:00,010 --> 00:11:00,610
of myself!

238
00:11:05,150 --> 00:11:05,650
Okay.

239
00:11:05,750 --> 00:11:07,000
I know. I know.

240
00:11:09,390 --> 00:11:11,320
I know you're feeling frustrated.

241
00:11:11,870 --> 00:11:12,820
If it really doesn't work out,

242
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:14,830
just treat it as a trip to Beijing

243
00:11:15,220 --> 00:11:16,280
to clear your mind,

244
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:17,150
okay?

245
00:11:19,150 --> 00:11:20,170
On the way,

246
00:11:20,340 --> 00:11:21,220
take good care of yourself

247
00:11:21,220 --> 00:11:22,220
and watch your bags.

248
00:11:22,220 --> 00:11:24,150
It's your first time leaving home.

249
00:11:24,530 --> 00:11:27,620
Mom, I'm almost 30.

250
00:11:37,390 --> 00:11:38,450
Alright, alright.

251
00:11:38,770 --> 00:11:40,630
Go on. Everyone else is boarding.

252
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:43,850
I'm going then, Mom.

253
00:11:45,530 --> 00:11:46,280
Take care.

254
00:11:49,630 --> 00:11:50,630
Mom, go back home.

255
00:11:50,770 --> 00:11:52,060
Get on. Get on.

256
00:12:07,610 --> 00:12:08,450
Excuse me.

257
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,030
Well, I need to put my bag up.

258
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:13,410
Make sure that the suitcase is secure.

259
00:12:16,210 --> 00:12:16,810
Excuse me.

260
00:12:19,220 --> 00:12:21,100
I put a thermos cup in your bag.

261
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:22,320
Once the train starts,

262
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:23,700
go get some hot water.

263
00:12:23,790 --> 00:12:25,510
I know, Mom.

264
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:28,100
I'll call you when I get there.

265
00:12:29,390 --> 00:12:30,820
Once you're settled, tell me

266
00:12:30,820 --> 00:12:31,620
your address.

267
00:12:36,890 --> 00:12:38,170
Visitors seeing passengers off,

268
00:12:38,170 --> 00:12:39,230
please stand back!

269
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:40,650
The train is about to depart!

270
00:12:40,650 --> 00:12:41,340
Go back.

271
00:12:44,370 --> 00:12:45,390
Mom, go on back.

272
00:12:46,860 --> 00:12:47,840
Go home. Go home.

273
00:12:50,530 --> 00:12:51,060
Bye-bye.

274
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:53,120
Bye-bye.

275
00:12:54,170 --> 00:12:55,030
Good luck, son.

276
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:56,460
I'll do my best.

277
00:12:57,410 --> 00:12:58,140
You can do it.

278
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,300
Hurry back!

279
00:14:27,160 --> 00:14:30,790
[Beijing Station]

280
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:42,790
Sir,

281
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,390
looking for a place to stay?

282
00:14:44,390 --> 00:14:45,420
My place is huge!

283
00:14:45,460 --> 00:14:46,260
Lots of space,

284
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:47,010
with big beds, too!

285
00:14:46,900 --> 00:14:47,530
[Jiale Hotel]

286
00:14:47,150 --> 00:14:48,480
The quilts are all brand new.

287
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:49,330
Soft and fluffy.

288
00:14:49,260 --> 00:14:51,850
[Beijing Station]

289
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:50,630
Sir, our beds are so comfy—

290
00:14:50,630 --> 00:14:51,940
it's like sleeping on a cloud.

291
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:53,360
Guaranteed sweet dreams every night.

292
00:14:51,990 --> 00:14:53,390
[Jiale Hotel]

293
00:14:53,650 --> 00:14:54,000
Then,

294
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,170
how much is the rent?

295
00:14:56,010 --> 00:14:56,910
Pay whatever feels right to you.

296
00:14:56,910 --> 00:14:57,920
Whatever you think is fair.

297
00:14:57,160 --> 00:14:57,720
[Jiale Hotel]

298
00:14:58,010 --> 00:14:59,370
Well, let me take you
to check it out first,

299
00:14:59,370 --> 00:14:59,790
okay?

300
00:14:59,860 --> 00:15:00,820
What do you think you're doing?

301
00:15:00,820 --> 00:15:01,840
Ever heard of first come, first served?

302
00:15:00,890 --> 00:15:02,030
[Changxing Hotel]

303
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,440
I saw him first, but I was slow!

304
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,440
Which eye of yours saw him first?

305
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:05,750
-Sir, come with me.
-Go away!

306
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:06,540
[Beijing Station]

307
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:06,390
Sir.

308
00:15:06,410 --> 00:15:07,670
Come on, sir, let's go!

309
00:15:07,670 --> 00:15:09,130
Are you snatching his bag?

310
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:10,960
What are you doing

311
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:12,530
in broad daylight?

312
00:15:12,530 --> 00:15:13,840
Where do you think this is?

313
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:15,650
You think you two can act wild here,

314
00:15:15,650 --> 00:15:17,250
fighting like cats and dogs?

315
00:15:17,630 --> 00:15:18,460
Little Northeasterner,

316
00:15:18,460 --> 00:15:19,320
no one gets on my nerves

317
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:20,460
like you do.

318
00:15:20,460 --> 00:15:21,270
I'm telling you,

319
00:15:21,270 --> 00:15:22,870
you're not getting a piece of this today!

320
00:15:22,870 --> 00:15:24,100
What's it got to do with you?

321
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:25,430
You skinny beanpole.

322
00:15:25,460 --> 00:15:25,910
Hurry up.

323
00:15:25,570 --> 00:15:29,040
[Beijing Station]

324
00:15:25,910 --> 00:15:26,770
Scram!

325
00:15:27,030 --> 00:15:27,480
Sir.

326
00:15:27,630 --> 00:15:28,890
Still won't stop, huh?

327
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:30,700
Am I talking to a wall?

328
00:15:30,860 --> 00:15:31,630
What are you doing?

329
00:15:31,630 --> 00:15:32,510
Dragging and pulling him like that—

330
00:15:32,510 --> 00:15:33,150
just snatching him like goods?

331
00:15:33,150 --> 00:15:34,530
Don't push your luck!

332
00:15:34,620 --> 00:15:35,380
Sir.

333
00:15:35,170 --> 00:15:39,470
[Beijing Station]

334
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:38,240
The police are right over there!

335
00:15:38,340 --> 00:15:39,600
That little guesthouse operation of yours,

336
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:40,080
what?

337
00:15:40,170 --> 00:15:41,500
You don't want to stay in business, huh?

338
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:42,860
What did you say? Say that again!

339
00:15:42,860 --> 00:15:43,320
Come on!

340
00:15:43,340 --> 00:15:45,070
Let's go to the police station!

341
00:15:48,700 --> 00:15:49,860
Fine, Little Northeasterner.

342
00:15:49,860 --> 00:15:50,660
You're tough.

343
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:52,370
Keep this up!

344
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:53,740
Just you wait!

345
00:15:53,770 --> 00:15:54,700
I'll be waiting!

346
00:15:58,480 --> 00:16:00,610
Come on, come on, take a look over here!

347
00:16:01,840 --> 00:16:02,440
Thank you.

348
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:03,500
No problem.

349
00:16:03,740 --> 00:16:04,600
New to Beijing?

350
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:04,980
Yes.

351
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,010
Need a place to stay?

352
00:16:06,010 --> 00:16:06,480
Yes.

353
00:16:06,510 --> 00:16:08,240
I'd rather look around myself.

354
00:16:09,550 --> 00:16:09,980
My place is close to

355
00:16:09,980 --> 00:16:11,360
the Capital Film Studio!

356
00:16:10,290 --> 00:16:12,070
[Beijing Station]

357
00:16:12,130 --> 00:16:13,390
Just two streets away!

358
00:16:15,290 --> 00:16:16,510
How did you know I was going to

359
00:16:16,510 --> 00:16:17,770
the Capital Film Studio?

360
00:16:17,770 --> 00:16:19,270
You artsy types—

361
00:16:19,270 --> 00:16:21,200
your artistic vibe just radiates!

362
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:24,840
Which hotel are you from?

363
00:16:25,140 --> 00:16:26,890
[Accommodation] [Seasons Change]
[Accommodation & Reception]

364
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:26,990
Seasons Change Grand Hotel.

365
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:28,440
No,

366
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:29,860
I can't afford a big hotel.

367
00:16:29,860 --> 00:16:31,190
A watermelon looks big—

368
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,650
not to an elephant.

369
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,220
A sesame seed looks tiny—

370
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:35,460
not to an ant.

371
00:16:35,980 --> 00:16:37,770
You've got an interesting way of talking.

372
00:16:37,770 --> 00:16:38,500
Relativity.

373
00:16:38,620 --> 00:16:39,860
Never mind the theory.

374
00:16:39,860 --> 00:16:41,100
The rent for a bed at my place

375
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:42,100
is just a few yuan.

376
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:43,910
You'll definitely like it.

377
00:16:43,910 --> 00:16:44,960
Come on.

378
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:46,250
I've been checking along the way,

379
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:47,940
and the rent is either 10 or 15 yuan.

380
00:16:47,940 --> 00:16:48,860
"Just a few yuan"—

381
00:16:48,860 --> 00:16:50,440
how much is the rent exactly?

382
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:51,820
"A few" means under 10.

383
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:53,410
Go check out my place!

384
00:16:53,410 --> 00:16:54,600
Perfect fit for someone like you!

385
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:57,260
If you're not satisfied,
you don't have to stay!

386
00:16:57,530 --> 00:16:58,650
T-Then it's a deal.

387
00:16:59,150 --> 00:17:00,810
I'll just go take a look first,

388
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:02,500
and I'll decide after I see it!

389
00:17:02,510 --> 00:17:03,890
If it's even one yuan more than you said,

390
00:17:03,890 --> 00:17:04,790
I-I'm leaving.

391
00:17:04,790 --> 00:17:05,720
You can't stop me.

392
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:09,050
If I wanted to cheat you,
why would I have helped you just now?

393
00:17:09,930 --> 00:17:13,240
[Accommodation] [Seasons Change]
[Accommodation & Reception]

394
00:17:13,290 --> 00:17:16,930
[Welcome to Seasons Change Grand Hotel]

395
00:17:16,609 --> 00:17:17,940
Put your luggage inside.

396
00:17:17,940 --> 00:17:19,200
And wait for me a while.

397
00:17:19,329 --> 00:17:21,250
I'm going to round up a few more guests.

398
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:21,829
It's not worth the trip

399
00:17:21,829 --> 00:17:22,890
for just one guest.

400
00:17:23,140 --> 00:17:23,520
Okay.

401
00:17:23,700 --> 00:17:24,900
Wait here for me a bit!

402
00:17:27,740 --> 00:17:31,430
[Welcome to Seasons Change Grand Hotel]

403
00:17:51,510 --> 00:17:52,600
Sir, a map, please.

404
00:17:54,510 --> 00:17:55,180
Thanks!

405
00:17:54,780 --> 00:17:55,990
[Beijing Travel & Transportation Map]

406
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:27,790
Thief!

407
00:18:27,830 --> 00:18:28,760
Stop that thief!

408
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:42,910
Make way! Make way!

409
00:18:43,250 --> 00:18:43,960
Make way!

410
00:18:45,850 --> 00:18:46,770
Where's my bag?

411
00:18:46,830 --> 00:18:47,630
Hurry, get up!

412
00:18:48,880 --> 00:18:49,950
Where's my bag?

413
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:50,940
-He stole my bag!
-Stay still!

414
00:18:50,940 --> 00:18:51,510
Stay still!

415
00:18:51,510 --> 00:18:52,920
Officers, he stole my bag!

416
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:53,850
He stole her bag!

417
00:18:54,030 --> 00:18:54,440
Speak!

418
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:55,580
Where is my bag?

419
00:18:55,830 --> 00:18:56,610
What are you gonna do about it?

420
00:18:55,940 --> 00:18:59,650
[Household Registration Office]
[Case Handling Office]

421
00:18:57,420 --> 00:18:57,920
Shut up!

422
00:19:03,030 --> 00:19:03,560
Alright.

423
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:05,180
They are

424
00:19:05,290 --> 00:19:05,940
a gang.

425
00:19:06,530 --> 00:19:08,130
How much cash was in your bag?

426
00:19:09,140 --> 00:19:09,940
Two thousand.

427
00:19:10,030 --> 00:19:10,830
Two thousand?

428
00:19:14,700 --> 00:19:15,500
What on earth?

429
00:19:15,880 --> 00:19:17,680
Why did you carry that much cash?

430
00:19:18,350 --> 00:19:20,950
T-That was for
my living expenses and tuition.

431
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:22,510
I want to audition
for a song and dance troupe here.

432
00:19:22,510 --> 00:19:23,800
I need to take classes.

433
00:19:26,350 --> 00:19:27,140
Officer...

434
00:19:28,290 --> 00:19:29,220
What should I do?

435
00:19:30,140 --> 00:19:30,770
Here's what we'll do.

436
00:19:30,770 --> 00:19:32,000
Write down your address

437
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:32,790
and phone number.

438
00:19:32,790 --> 00:19:35,720
If there's any update,
we'll contact you right away.

439
00:19:37,570 --> 00:19:39,500
I haven't found a place to stay yet.

440
00:19:39,980 --> 00:19:42,240
And I don't have a contact number either.

441
00:19:46,770 --> 00:19:48,160
Then what are you going to do now?

442
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:49,720
How about contacting your family

443
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:51,350
and asking them to wire some money first?

444
00:19:51,350 --> 00:19:52,140
I can't

445
00:19:52,330 --> 00:19:53,790
tell my family about this.

446
00:19:58,110 --> 00:19:59,750
Now don't panic.

447
00:20:01,070 --> 00:20:01,870
I understand—

448
00:20:02,050 --> 00:20:04,380
it's really not easy
for you out-of-towners

449
00:20:04,380 --> 00:20:05,110
coming here.

450
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:07,340
In Beijing,

451
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,260
remember this:

452
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:11,810
if you're in trouble, find the police.

453
00:20:11,850 --> 00:20:13,180
This is the station's number.

454
00:20:13,180 --> 00:20:14,880
Once you've settled somewhere,

455
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,300
call me and let me know.

456
00:20:17,010 --> 00:20:17,720
Okay, okay.

457
00:20:18,220 --> 00:20:19,050
Please, I'm counting on you.

458
00:20:19,050 --> 00:20:20,290
You have to help me find it!

459
00:20:20,290 --> 00:20:20,920
Don't worry.

460
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:21,920
He won't get away.

461
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:24,050
Hello?

462
00:20:26,570 --> 00:20:28,030
Okay, I'll be right there.

463
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:32,760
Alright, stop crying. Calm down now.

464
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:34,440
This young man here is a good guy.

465
00:20:34,440 --> 00:20:35,640
He stepped in to help.

466
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:36,350
Nowadays,

467
00:20:37,070 --> 00:20:38,600
there aren't many like you.

468
00:20:38,700 --> 00:20:40,230
It was the right thing to do!

469
00:20:40,290 --> 00:20:41,950
I'm counting on you, Officer!

470
00:20:48,140 --> 00:20:48,740
Thank you.

471
00:20:49,500 --> 00:20:50,360
It was nothing.

472
00:20:55,550 --> 00:20:57,370
[Welcome to Beijing]

473
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:56,850
Thank you, sir.

474
00:20:57,350 --> 00:20:58,070
Don't mention it.

475
00:20:57,370 --> 00:20:58,890
[Exit]

476
00:20:58,250 --> 00:20:59,710
I didn't really help much.

477
00:21:00,290 --> 00:21:02,390
It's just that your loss is huge.

478
00:21:03,380 --> 00:21:05,580
I'll just have to chalk it up to bad luck.

479
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:06,550
Do you have any relatives

480
00:21:06,550 --> 00:21:07,790
or friends in Beijing?

481
00:21:07,790 --> 00:21:09,120
Do you have a place to go?

482
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:09,720
No.

483
00:21:14,290 --> 00:21:15,790
When I arrived at the station,

484
00:21:15,790 --> 00:21:17,240
I noticed there was

485
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:18,240
a state-run guesthouse over there.

486
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:19,250
It's only about 10 yuan a day.

487
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:23,490
[Welcome to Beijing]

488
00:21:19,830 --> 00:21:20,610
How about this—

489
00:21:20,610 --> 00:21:21,740
get settled first.

490
00:21:21,830 --> 00:21:23,030
Then let your family know you're safe.

491
00:21:23,030 --> 00:21:24,140
Take the 50 yuan first.

492
00:21:24,140 --> 00:21:24,600
No need!

493
00:21:24,810 --> 00:21:25,610
I really don't.

494
00:21:25,610 --> 00:21:26,070
No need?

495
00:21:26,550 --> 00:21:27,880
Y-You still have money?

496
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:29,050
Where will you stay?

497
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:31,030
Are you going to sleep in the square?

498
00:21:31,030 --> 00:21:32,570
A girl like you out on your own—

499
00:21:32,570 --> 00:21:34,170
your family must be worried.

500
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:35,550
Get settled first.

501
00:21:35,810 --> 00:21:37,180
Then let your family know you're safe.

502
00:21:37,180 --> 00:21:37,640
Take it.

503
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,660
I'll definitely pay you back.

504
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:47,610
I'll pay you back tomorrow!

505
00:21:47,610 --> 00:21:48,940
Where would you find me?

506
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:50,090
I don't even know

507
00:21:50,090 --> 00:21:51,480
where I'll be staying yet.

508
00:21:51,480 --> 00:21:53,480
Then let's meet back here tomorrow!

509
00:21:54,850 --> 00:21:56,920
Really, no need. It's not much.

510
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:58,900
[Welcome to Beijing]

511
00:21:58,110 --> 00:21:58,570
Sir,

512
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:01,140
this... may not be worth much,

513
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:02,260
but take it

514
00:22:02,380 --> 00:22:03,240
as collateral.

515
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:07,570
Okay.

516
00:22:09,310 --> 00:22:10,010
We're both out here

517
00:22:10,010 --> 00:22:11,550
taking our chances in Beijing.

518
00:22:11,550 --> 00:22:12,180
Take care.

519
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:14,530
I've got to go.

520
00:22:14,530 --> 00:22:15,900
The car's been waiting for me for a while.

521
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:16,250
Okay.

522
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,180
Thank you, sir!

523
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:19,200
It's nothing!

524
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:20,200
See you tomorrow!

525
00:22:42,270 --> 00:22:43,270
Buddy! Over here!

526
00:22:44,290 --> 00:22:44,740
Sir.

527
00:22:45,880 --> 00:22:47,310
-Where did you go?
-Sorry, sorry.

528
00:22:47,310 --> 00:22:49,070
I already sent some guests to the hotel
and came back.

529
00:22:49,070 --> 00:22:50,270
I thought you'd run off.

530
00:22:50,270 --> 00:22:51,160
No, no, I wouldn't do that.

531
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:51,960
Hurry up and get in.

532
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:53,070
It'll be dinner time
by the time we get there.

533
00:22:53,070 --> 00:22:54,130
Alright, alright.

534
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:55,900
Nice sunglasses!

535
00:23:00,730 --> 00:23:02,740
[Hotel; Seasons Change]

536
00:23:11,220 --> 00:23:12,480
First time in Beijing?

537
00:23:12,900 --> 00:23:13,900
Yeah, first time!

538
00:23:14,330 --> 00:23:16,060
Then you gotta take a good look.

539
00:23:16,460 --> 00:23:17,440
If Beijing

540
00:23:16,690 --> 00:23:18,720
[Long Live the Great Unity
of the People of the World]

541
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:18,640
is the heart of the nation,

542
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:19,250
then right here

543
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:20,550
[Long live the People's Republic of China]

544
00:23:19,250 --> 00:23:20,610
is the very core of that heart.

545
00:23:20,610 --> 00:23:22,540
I love going down Chang'an Avenue.

546
00:23:23,010 --> 00:23:24,660
I just love looking at Chairman Mao.

547
00:23:24,660 --> 00:23:25,740
Seeing him makes me happy.

548
00:23:25,740 --> 00:23:26,540
Are you happy?

549
00:23:26,610 --> 00:23:27,810
I'm happy.

550
00:23:31,110 --> 00:23:33,610
[Hotel; Seasons Change]

551
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:48,980
Your stuff! Don't forget your stuff!

552
00:23:50,510 --> 00:23:50,960
Let me check

553
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:52,420
if I left anything behind.

554
00:23:55,740 --> 00:23:57,660
Little Northeasterner, you're back.

555
00:23:57,660 --> 00:23:58,320
Having fun?

556
00:24:06,740 --> 00:24:07,940
This is Luogu Hutong!

557
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:10,120
We're living in a hutong?

558
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:10,940
They're all

559
00:24:10,940 --> 00:24:12,000
shared courtyards in the hutongs.

560
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,200
Ours is a two-courtyard house.

561
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:15,260
Look at the gate. It's centuries old!

562
00:24:15,270 --> 00:24:16,000
Back in the day,

563
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,240
only princes or nobles could live here.

564
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:19,050
Now ordinary folks like us
can live here too.

565
00:24:19,050 --> 00:24:19,580
Wang,

566
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:20,770
tending your flowers?

567
00:24:20,770 --> 00:24:22,160
Northeasterner, come look at my flowers!

568
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:23,000
How are they?

569
00:24:23,410 --> 00:24:24,290
I remember this one

570
00:24:24,290 --> 00:24:25,310
hadn't bloomed yesterday.

571
00:24:25,310 --> 00:24:26,510
It just opened today.

572
00:24:26,660 --> 00:24:27,920
I'll snatch one later.

573
00:24:27,920 --> 00:24:29,500
Don't you dare!

574
00:24:31,030 --> 00:24:32,980
One of our old neighbors.
Really interesting guy.

575
00:24:32,980 --> 00:24:34,280
Ma, cooking alone?

576
00:24:34,810 --> 00:24:36,200
My wife hasn't come back yet.

577
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:37,140
Gotta have a couple of drinks then.

578
00:24:37,140 --> 00:24:38,500
Absolutely. Come by when you have time.

579
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:39,900
Little Northeasterner,

580
00:24:40,250 --> 00:24:41,420
I've been waiting for you.

581
00:24:41,420 --> 00:24:42,350
What for?

582
00:24:42,550 --> 00:24:43,310
Didn't you say that

583
00:24:43,310 --> 00:24:45,570
my braised pork yesterday was too salty?

584
00:24:45,570 --> 00:24:47,170
I just mentioned it offhand.

585
00:24:47,420 --> 00:24:48,400
Try it again today

586
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:49,860
and see how I did this time.

587
00:24:49,940 --> 00:24:50,900
Why don't you have a bite too?

588
00:24:50,900 --> 00:24:52,100
No thanks, I'll pass.

589
00:24:52,270 --> 00:24:53,790
Hurry up, come on.

590
00:24:53,790 --> 00:24:54,720
Then, go straight ahead.

591
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:55,700
See that sign ahead?

592
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:56,360
Turn right.

593
00:24:56,940 --> 00:24:58,050
I'll meet you out front in a minute.

594
00:24:58,050 --> 00:24:58,420
Okay.

595
00:24:58,750 --> 00:24:59,570
Let me try the pork.

596
00:24:59,570 --> 00:25:00,610
-Come on.
-Let me.

597
00:25:01,380 --> 00:25:01,890
How is it?

598
00:25:01,820 --> 00:25:07,670
[Seasons Change Hotel]

599
00:25:02,380 --> 00:25:04,240
It's not salty today. A bit sweet.

600
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:05,680
Yesterday too salty, today too sweet,

601
00:25:05,680 --> 00:25:06,140
huh?

602
00:25:06,290 --> 00:25:07,610
You're so picky.

603
00:25:20,610 --> 00:25:21,220
Uncle,

604
00:25:21,460 --> 00:25:23,190
why are you filming the hutong?

605
00:25:23,220 --> 00:25:24,820
The scenery's so beautiful.

606
00:25:25,460 --> 00:25:27,250
You're here to stay at the hotel, right?

607
00:25:27,250 --> 00:25:28,270
It's in there.

608
00:25:28,830 --> 00:25:29,680
Okay, thanks.

609
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:30,290
Here.

610
00:25:30,420 --> 00:25:30,950
Hee-yur.

611
00:25:30,980 --> 00:25:32,510
It's "Here," not "Hee-yur."

612
00:25:32,510 --> 00:25:33,740
Look at here!

613
00:25:33,830 --> 00:25:34,510
Here!

614
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:35,840
H-e-r-e,

615
00:25:35,860 --> 00:25:36,660
Here!

616
00:25:36,680 --> 00:25:37,770
Hee-yur.

617
00:25:37,790 --> 00:25:38,460
Here.

618
00:25:38,460 --> 00:25:40,720
What's with all this "Here" and "Hee-yur"?

619
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:42,220
Uncle, look at this word.

620
00:25:42,310 --> 00:25:44,640
Should we pronounce "Here" or "Hee-yur"?

621
00:25:44,720 --> 00:25:45,700
Here.

622
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:47,310
H-e-r-e, Here!

623
00:25:47,460 --> 00:25:49,360
Right. H-e-r-e, Here.

624
00:25:49,920 --> 00:25:50,920
Hee-yur.

625
00:25:51,330 --> 00:25:52,880
-Here.
-Are you a local here?

626
00:25:52,880 --> 00:25:53,770
No, I'm not.

627
00:25:54,810 --> 00:25:56,770
Let me teach you a Beijing phrase then.

628
00:25:56,770 --> 00:25:57,830
Sure.

629
00:25:57,900 --> 00:25:59,230
Mind your own business.

630
00:25:59,980 --> 00:26:01,780
Fine, I won't.

631
00:26:01,900 --> 00:26:03,740
The whole courtyard could hear you.

632
00:26:03,740 --> 00:26:04,800
What are you doing?

633
00:26:05,570 --> 00:26:06,290
Who are you?

634
00:26:07,090 --> 00:26:08,690
I'm here to stay at the hotel.

635
00:26:08,980 --> 00:26:09,610
"Seasons Change"?

636
00:26:09,610 --> 00:26:10,010
Right.

637
00:26:10,160 --> 00:26:10,820
Over there.

638
00:26:11,090 --> 00:26:11,550
Thanks.

639
00:26:11,830 --> 00:26:13,250
What's all this "here" or "there"?

640
00:26:13,250 --> 00:26:15,030
Is it "Here" or "Hee-yur"?

641
00:26:15,570 --> 00:26:16,390
Hee-yur.

642
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:17,300
Young man!

643
00:26:19,770 --> 00:26:20,830
Where are you from?

644
00:26:21,030 --> 00:26:22,090
Yantai, Shandong.

645
00:26:22,790 --> 00:26:23,790
By the sea, right?

646
00:26:24,750 --> 00:26:25,610
How old are you?

647
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:26,730
Twenty-six.

648
00:26:28,830 --> 00:26:29,760
Came here alone?

649
00:26:31,310 --> 00:26:31,920
I'm

650
00:26:32,050 --> 00:26:33,660
the head of
the Neighborhood Committee here.

651
00:26:33,660 --> 00:26:34,460
Hello, hello.

652
00:26:34,530 --> 00:26:35,790
Since you're new here,

653
00:26:36,090 --> 00:26:37,890
you must register with us first.

654
00:26:38,790 --> 00:26:40,720
For national peace and stability,

655
00:26:40,750 --> 00:26:41,150
right?

656
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:42,720
Law and order, the long-term security,

657
00:26:42,720 --> 00:26:44,120
depend on every one of us.

658
00:26:44,240 --> 00:26:44,680
Understood!

659
00:26:44,680 --> 00:26:45,080
Right?

660
00:26:46,070 --> 00:26:47,530
Go register with us first.

661
00:26:47,940 --> 00:26:49,000
Who brought you here?

662
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:49,980
Little Northeasterner.

663
00:26:49,980 --> 00:26:51,220
Where is he then?

664
00:26:51,740 --> 00:26:52,070
He...

665
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:52,840
Director Li!

666
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:54,890
How did this end up disturbing you?

667
00:26:55,140 --> 00:26:56,840
He's new here.

668
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:57,640
You...

669
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:58,750
You let him wander around alone.

670
00:26:58,750 --> 00:26:59,980
If something happens,
will you take responsibility?

671
00:26:59,980 --> 00:27:00,920
Wang Yunfang insisted I

672
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:02,120
try her braised pork.

673
00:27:02,510 --> 00:27:03,940
Besides, with you watching over here,

674
00:27:03,940 --> 00:27:05,050
the security in this area

675
00:27:04,850 --> 00:27:08,570
[Seasons Change Hotel]

676
00:27:05,050 --> 00:27:06,310
is famously good.

677
00:27:06,350 --> 00:27:07,610
You and your sweet talk!

678
00:27:07,610 --> 00:27:08,330
I'm telling you,

679
00:27:08,330 --> 00:27:09,240
stop making me worry about you

680
00:27:09,240 --> 00:27:10,070
all the time.

681
00:27:10,330 --> 00:27:10,880
Remember to register.

682
00:27:10,880 --> 00:27:11,610
Don't worry.

683
00:27:11,720 --> 00:27:13,050
Go back and have dinner.

684
00:27:13,500 --> 00:27:14,360
Leave him to me.

685
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:15,560
This is it!

686
00:27:16,010 --> 00:27:17,270
Seasons Change Hotel.

687
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:19,680
In all of old Beijing,

688
00:27:20,180 --> 00:27:21,220
you won't find

689
00:27:21,030 --> 00:27:30,280
[Seasons Change Hotel]

690
00:27:21,270 --> 00:27:23,000
a courtyard this comfortable!

691
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:34,320
I live in this gate lodge.

692
00:27:34,460 --> 00:27:35,660
There's a phone here.

693
00:27:35,790 --> 00:27:36,590
The front gate

694
00:27:36,590 --> 00:27:38,180
locks every night at 11.

695
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:39,180
If you come back late,

696
00:27:39,180 --> 00:27:40,330
don't blame me for not letting you in.

697
00:27:40,330 --> 00:27:40,700
Okay.

698
00:27:41,830 --> 00:27:42,700
We have a new guest?

699
00:27:42,700 --> 00:27:43,100
Hello.

700
00:27:43,310 --> 00:27:45,090
Whose stinky shoes are in the hallway?

701
00:27:45,090 --> 00:27:46,220
What's wrong, guys?

702
00:27:46,350 --> 00:27:46,740
Luo,

703
00:27:46,830 --> 00:27:47,700
didn't you say nothing should be left in

704
00:27:47,700 --> 00:27:48,500
common areas?

705
00:27:48,530 --> 00:27:49,610
I'm clearing it all out today.

706
00:27:49,610 --> 00:27:50,330
Hurry up.

707
00:27:51,070 --> 00:27:51,420
Alright.

708
00:27:51,420 --> 00:27:52,750
Clear out the fire exit.

709
00:27:53,030 --> 00:27:53,900
People living here come

710
00:27:53,900 --> 00:27:54,960
from every corner of the country.

711
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:56,000
North, south, all around.

712
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:57,660
Some are here
visiting relatives or friends.

713
00:27:57,660 --> 00:27:59,380
There're also tourists,
business travelers,

714
00:27:59,380 --> 00:28:00,720
fortune seekers, and dreamers.

715
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:01,920
Fate brought us

716
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:02,660
together.

717
00:28:03,140 --> 00:28:04,070
After living here for a while,

718
00:28:04,070 --> 00:28:05,160
we've become like family.

719
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:05,570
Look.

720
00:28:06,030 --> 00:28:07,070
This area

721
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,060
is for cooking.

722
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:09,790
Everyone cooks together.

723
00:28:09,790 --> 00:28:10,520
Isn't it fun?

724
00:28:11,350 --> 00:28:12,480
What are you making?

725
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:13,880
Pork with chili peppers.

726
00:28:14,160 --> 00:28:15,420
Isn't this a cold dish?

727
00:28:15,500 --> 00:28:16,750
I'm preparing to make it.

728
00:28:16,750 --> 00:28:17,440
Fried sauce noodles?

729
00:28:17,440 --> 00:28:17,850
Right.

730
00:28:18,010 --> 00:28:18,340
Okay.

731
00:28:18,740 --> 00:28:19,980
Save a bowl for me today,

732
00:28:19,980 --> 00:28:20,250
is that okay?

733
00:28:20,250 --> 00:28:20,850
You got it.

734
00:28:20,900 --> 00:28:22,090
Next time I cook, I'll save you a bowl.

735
00:28:22,090 --> 00:28:22,500
Okay.

736
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:24,460
You provide the noodles,
and I'll bring the garlic!

737
00:28:24,460 --> 00:28:24,990
Alright.

738
00:28:26,030 --> 00:28:26,480
We have

739
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:28,050
24-hour hot water!

740
00:28:28,590 --> 00:28:30,700
This water isn't hot enough
to make instant noodles!

741
00:28:30,700 --> 00:28:32,200
It takes time to boil, eh?

742
00:28:32,830 --> 00:28:34,460
Get yourself a thermos bottle later.

743
00:28:34,460 --> 00:28:35,400
When there is hot water,

744
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:36,420
just store some, and you're set.

745
00:28:36,420 --> 00:28:36,750
Okay.

746
00:28:37,610 --> 00:28:39,270
Here! Women's bathroom!

747
00:28:40,460 --> 00:28:41,850
There, the men's bathroom!

748
00:28:41,850 --> 00:28:43,310
You can wash clothes here.

749
00:28:44,460 --> 00:28:46,240
Come on, girls,

750
00:28:46,250 --> 00:28:47,830
once the clothes are dry, take them down!

751
00:28:47,830 --> 00:28:48,880
Don't leave them hanging
all over the place!

752
00:28:48,880 --> 00:28:50,500
It bothers me, you know?

753
00:28:51,460 --> 00:28:52,250
We've been a "model sanitation unit"

754
00:28:52,250 --> 00:28:52,940
every year!

755
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:54,400
Don't mess that up for me!

756
00:28:55,660 --> 00:28:56,030
Sis,

757
00:28:56,050 --> 00:28:56,830
I'm talking here.

758
00:28:56,830 --> 00:28:58,090
Can you do your vocalizing later?

759
00:28:58,090 --> 00:28:59,140
Thank you, sis.

760
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:02,880
Small but fully equipped.

761
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:05,090
That little courtyard upstairs
looks small, right?

762
00:29:05,090 --> 00:29:07,110
Big enough to run a racehorse ragged.

763
00:29:07,110 --> 00:29:08,220
And even down in the basement,

764
00:29:08,220 --> 00:29:10,350
a thousand-year pine could take root.

765
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:11,130
On that side—

766
00:29:11,180 --> 00:29:12,710
there're 28 rooms in total.

767
00:29:13,330 --> 00:29:14,070
Keep moving

768
00:29:14,290 --> 00:29:14,980
and turn left—

769
00:29:14,980 --> 00:29:16,110
there's a fire exit.

770
00:29:21,850 --> 00:29:22,880
This way, this way!

771
00:29:22,880 --> 00:29:24,680
You're not staying on that side!

772
00:29:27,960 --> 00:29:28,480
See?

773
00:29:29,460 --> 00:29:31,260
Room 108—"fortune all the way."

774
00:29:31,510 --> 00:29:32,310
Lucky, right?

775
00:29:32,610 --> 00:29:33,440
Very lucky.

776
00:29:33,610 --> 00:29:34,110
Well.

777
00:29:35,090 --> 00:29:35,690
Here we go.

778
00:29:37,740 --> 00:29:39,380
Everyone who comes to Beijing

779
00:29:39,380 --> 00:29:40,710
wants to put down roots.

780
00:29:40,960 --> 00:29:41,680
But that's all talk

781
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:43,540
until you've found your footing.

782
00:29:43,880 --> 00:29:45,250
Beijing is enormous.

783
00:29:45,830 --> 00:29:46,770
If you can just have a place

784
00:29:46,770 --> 00:29:48,000
and a bed of your own,

785
00:29:48,250 --> 00:29:49,440
you'll feel secure.

786
00:29:49,480 --> 00:29:49,800
Yes.

787
00:29:49,960 --> 00:29:50,880
Everyone in this room

788
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:52,140
is in the arts.

789
00:29:52,700 --> 00:29:53,500
This guy in this bed...

790
00:29:53,500 --> 00:29:54,100
Come look.

791
00:29:55,590 --> 00:29:56,450
Great painter!

792
00:29:57,160 --> 00:29:57,960
In the making.

793
00:29:58,640 --> 00:30:00,170
From Shanxi. Name's Cao Ye.

794
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:02,700
He's a bit eccentric.

795
00:30:03,420 --> 00:30:04,480
Look at the pets he keeps.

796
00:30:04,480 --> 00:30:06,510
They're different from everyone else's.

797
00:30:06,510 --> 00:30:07,970
And this one in this bed...

798
00:30:08,500 --> 00:30:09,230
A Beijinger!

799
00:30:10,850 --> 00:30:11,720
Tao Liangliang.

800
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:12,790
I call him Mr. Tao.

801
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:14,130
He's a musician—

802
00:30:14,550 --> 00:30:15,750
plays the saxophone.

803
00:30:16,010 --> 00:30:18,380
He's been trying to get into
a song and dance troupe.

804
00:30:18,380 --> 00:30:20,070
Wait, he... he's a Beijinger.

805
00:30:20,140 --> 00:30:21,420
Why is he staying here then?

806
00:30:21,420 --> 00:30:21,950
See that?

807
00:30:22,220 --> 00:30:23,420
Even a born-and-bred Beijinger stays here.

808
00:30:23,420 --> 00:30:25,070
That's enough to show
it's comfortable here.

809
00:30:25,070 --> 00:30:25,800
A good place.

810
00:30:26,830 --> 00:30:27,890
The man in this bed—

811
00:30:28,610 --> 00:30:29,550
he's from Henan.

812
00:30:29,830 --> 00:30:30,960
Name's Guo Zongbao.

813
00:30:31,570 --> 00:30:32,250
I hear he used to

814
00:30:32,250 --> 00:30:33,180
perform Henan opera.

815
00:30:33,180 --> 00:30:34,180
Now he's an actor.

816
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:35,720
An actor?

817
00:30:36,110 --> 00:30:37,010
An extra, though.

818
00:30:37,010 --> 00:30:38,420
Occasionally gets a few lines.

819
00:30:38,420 --> 00:30:39,680
That's still an actor!

820
00:30:39,720 --> 00:30:40,310
Exactly!

821
00:30:41,140 --> 00:30:42,440
This is your bed!

822
00:30:44,030 --> 00:30:44,550
But... but...

823
00:30:44,550 --> 00:30:45,920
what about all this stuff?

824
00:30:45,920 --> 00:30:47,050
Move these things away,

825
00:30:47,050 --> 00:30:49,380
and your bed is
exactly the same as theirs.

826
00:30:50,900 --> 00:30:52,700
Alright, you've seen the place.

827
00:30:54,030 --> 00:30:54,790
This bed—

828
00:30:55,570 --> 00:30:57,290
six yuan a day.

829
00:30:59,240 --> 00:31:01,170
Rent is paid every 10 days minimum.

830
00:31:01,720 --> 00:31:03,110
Forty yuan for the deposit.

831
00:31:03,110 --> 00:31:04,140
When it's almost due,

832
00:31:04,140 --> 00:31:05,540
I'll remind you to renew.

833
00:31:07,050 --> 00:31:09,530
Anyway, if you don't want me nagging...

834
00:31:15,550 --> 00:31:15,920
Okay.

835
00:31:16,880 --> 00:31:17,940
Straightforward.

836
00:31:19,270 --> 00:31:20,640
You'll definitely

837
00:31:21,030 --> 00:31:22,050
strike some sparks

838
00:31:22,050 --> 00:31:23,250
living with this lot.

839
00:31:23,570 --> 00:31:24,830
What do you mean?

840
00:31:25,090 --> 00:31:26,290
Just let it sink in.

841
00:31:26,590 --> 00:31:27,590
After you move in,

842
00:31:27,610 --> 00:31:28,740
you can mull it over.

843
00:31:30,010 --> 00:31:31,140
Alright, that's it.

844
00:31:31,220 --> 00:31:31,660
Wait.

845
00:31:36,920 --> 00:31:38,200
This is a specialty from my hometown!

846
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:38,660
Take it.

847
00:31:38,750 --> 00:31:40,400
Well, I can't accept it.

848
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:40,900
Take it.

849
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:43,940
-We just met—how can I accept your gift?
-It's fine.

850
00:31:43,940 --> 00:31:45,670
Then I won't stand on ceremony.

851
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:46,930
Alright.

852
00:31:47,290 --> 00:31:48,550
As the seasons change,

853
00:31:49,030 --> 00:31:50,880
may your dreams come true!

854
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:52,880
My dreams will come true!

855
00:31:54,310 --> 00:31:55,550
Come up and register in a bit!

856
00:31:55,550 --> 00:31:56,080
Alright!

857
00:31:58,770 --> 00:31:59,830
Don't worry, Mom.

858
00:32:00,200 --> 00:32:02,060
I'm staying at a state-run hotel.

859
00:32:03,900 --> 00:32:05,300
The place is really nice.

860
00:32:07,250 --> 00:32:09,180
You didn't even bring many things.

861
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:10,810
Go buy yourself some clothes

862
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:14,050
[Nanpin General Store]

863
00:32:11,090 --> 00:32:12,480
and eat whatever you want.

864
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:14,080
Don't worry about the money.

865
00:32:14,660 --> 00:32:15,880
Why didn't you take the new clothes

866
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:17,000
I made for you?

867
00:32:17,440 --> 00:32:18,970
I'll mail them to you later.

868
00:32:19,610 --> 00:32:20,340
Don't worry.

869
00:32:20,610 --> 00:32:21,830
There's a customer waiting in the shop.

870
00:32:21,830 --> 00:32:22,680
I have to go.

871
00:32:24,590 --> 00:32:26,090
Sis, I'm off!

872
00:32:25,290 --> 00:32:28,260
[Nanpin General Store]

873
00:32:26,200 --> 00:32:26,800
Thank you.

874
00:32:28,370 --> 00:32:30,940
[Cai's Clothing Shop]

875
00:32:30,940 --> 00:32:32,310
[Meiqin's Tailor Shop]

876
00:32:32,290 --> 00:32:34,240
Sorry to keep you waiting.

877
00:32:34,330 --> 00:32:35,810
Went to call Zhuang Zhuang?

878
00:32:35,810 --> 00:32:36,240
Yes.

879
00:32:36,810 --> 00:32:37,420
What's wrong with the coat?

880
00:32:37,420 --> 00:32:37,880
Zhuang,

881
00:32:38,090 --> 00:32:38,740
I want to alter

882
00:32:38,740 --> 00:32:39,880
this coat again.

883
00:32:40,010 --> 00:32:40,880
Look at the collar—

884
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:41,830
can you change it

885
00:32:42,220 --> 00:32:43,020
to that style?

886
00:32:45,810 --> 00:32:46,350
Sure.

887
00:32:47,500 --> 00:32:48,770
Let me take your measurements again.

888
00:32:48,770 --> 00:32:49,160
Okay.

889
00:32:50,830 --> 00:32:52,360
I've made a few new designs.

890
00:32:52,380 --> 00:32:53,550
I think they'll suit you well.

891
00:32:53,550 --> 00:32:55,110
Do you want to try them on later?

892
00:32:55,110 --> 00:32:55,840
Another day.

893
00:32:58,240 --> 00:33:00,300
I have to say, you're really blessed.

894
00:33:00,850 --> 00:33:02,580
Second marriages aren't easy.

895
00:33:03,500 --> 00:33:04,770
Zhuang Zhuang has all grown up now.

896
00:33:04,770 --> 00:33:06,700
She's even made her way to Beijing.

897
00:33:07,350 --> 00:33:07,980
Ye!

898
00:33:13,220 --> 00:33:14,590
I've put the uniforms for Factory No. 6

899
00:33:14,590 --> 00:33:15,500
on the counter.

900
00:33:15,550 --> 00:33:16,290
Sort them by size

901
00:33:16,290 --> 00:33:17,620
and deliver them later.

902
00:33:18,280 --> 00:33:19,430
I'll be going now.

903
00:33:19,740 --> 00:33:20,270
Alright.

904
00:33:20,460 --> 00:33:20,980
Okay, take care.

905
00:33:20,980 --> 00:33:21,350
Okay.

906
00:33:21,380 --> 00:33:25,070
[Meiqin's Tailor Shop]

907
00:33:21,810 --> 00:33:22,410
Take care.

908
00:33:23,590 --> 00:33:24,310
Take care.

909
00:33:24,330 --> 00:33:24,700
Bye.

910
00:33:27,090 --> 00:33:27,660
Girl,

911
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:30,090
it's not good to
lie to your family like that.

912
00:33:30,090 --> 00:33:31,550
If you were my own daughter,

913
00:33:31,550 --> 00:33:32,680
I'd be worried sick.

914
00:33:33,030 --> 00:33:34,140
If my mom knew

915
00:33:34,140 --> 00:33:35,470
all my money was stolen,

916
00:33:36,010 --> 00:33:37,470
she'd be worried sick too.

917
00:33:40,240 --> 00:33:42,050
Then... have you decided

918
00:33:42,050 --> 00:33:43,510
what kind of room you want?

919
00:33:46,140 --> 00:33:48,790
[Standard Double Room]
[Standard Single Room]

920
00:33:47,720 --> 00:33:48,250
Ma'am,

921
00:33:48,740 --> 00:33:49,960
do you have

922
00:33:49,960 --> 00:33:51,090
any beds available

923
00:33:51,090 --> 00:33:52,330
in the standard quadruple rooms?

924
00:33:52,330 --> 00:33:53,140
No, all full.

925
00:33:53,400 --> 00:33:54,250
The cheapest one right now

926
00:33:54,250 --> 00:33:55,420
is the one for 20.

927
00:34:04,220 --> 00:34:05,010
Ma'am, could you tell me—

928
00:34:05,010 --> 00:34:05,900
are there any places nearby

929
00:34:05,900 --> 00:34:07,290
where I can find odd jobs?

930
00:34:07,290 --> 00:34:08,380
I'll do anything.

931
00:34:08,550 --> 00:34:10,150
There's a street in the back.

932
00:34:10,150 --> 00:34:12,260
It's got... small bookstores,

933
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:14,150
barbershops,

934
00:34:14,150 --> 00:34:14,949
snack stalls,

935
00:34:15,110 --> 00:34:16,770
general stores—everything.

936
00:34:16,820 --> 00:34:18,030
They're hiring temp workers every day.

937
00:34:18,030 --> 00:34:19,630
Why don't you go check it out?

938
00:34:19,840 --> 00:34:20,300
Okay.

939
00:34:20,510 --> 00:34:22,400
So, do you still want to stay here?

940
00:34:24,820 --> 00:34:26,030
I won't stay today.

941
00:34:26,530 --> 00:34:27,230
I'm going to see

942
00:34:27,230 --> 00:34:28,830
if I can find some work first.

943
00:34:29,530 --> 00:34:30,400
Oh, right, ma'am.

944
00:34:30,400 --> 00:34:31,900
Here's the money for the call.

945
00:34:31,900 --> 00:34:32,830
No need, no need.

946
00:34:33,010 --> 00:34:34,469
Pay me after you find a job.

947
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:36,340
It's fine. Go ahead.

948
00:34:38,460 --> 00:34:39,060
Thank you.

949
00:34:42,800 --> 00:34:43,460
Come on, Liangliang.

950
00:34:43,460 --> 00:34:45,440
Turning his bed over
is going a bit far, isn't it?

951
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:46,050
Zongbao,

952
00:34:46,070 --> 00:34:48,600
he just can't go around
bullying Heretic Cao!

953
00:34:56,260 --> 00:34:57,090
L-Looking for something?

954
00:34:57,090 --> 00:34:58,350
L-Let me help you guys!

955
00:35:03,340 --> 00:35:04,940
Nothing to look for anymore?

956
00:35:08,920 --> 00:35:10,320
You ruined the painting?

957
00:35:12,350 --> 00:35:13,210
I'm really sorry.

958
00:35:13,210 --> 00:35:14,260
I accidentally

959
00:35:14,260 --> 00:35:15,340
ruined this painting.

960
00:35:15,340 --> 00:35:15,670
Um...

961
00:35:15,670 --> 00:35:17,150
Um... Let me introduce myself.

962
00:35:17,150 --> 00:35:18,350
My name is Xu Shengli.

963
00:35:18,570 --> 00:35:20,010
I'm from Yantai, Shandong.

964
00:35:20,010 --> 00:35:21,900
I was removing all that stuff from my bed

965
00:35:21,900 --> 00:35:22,650
and accidentally

966
00:35:22,650 --> 00:35:23,850
ruined the painting.

967
00:35:24,130 --> 00:35:25,400
I just went out to buy some tape.

968
00:35:25,400 --> 00:35:25,960
I thought

969
00:35:26,230 --> 00:35:27,380
I could tape it back together.

970
00:35:27,380 --> 00:35:28,240
It can be fixed.

971
00:35:28,730 --> 00:35:29,660
What did you say?

972
00:35:31,590 --> 00:35:33,320
You want to tape this painting?

973
00:35:34,360 --> 00:35:34,960
Have you heard of

974
00:35:34,960 --> 00:35:36,070
the "Mona Lisa"?

975
00:35:37,130 --> 00:35:37,930
Y-Yes, I have.

976
00:35:38,010 --> 00:35:38,810
This painting

977
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:40,570
was created by me,

978
00:35:40,590 --> 00:35:41,210
Cao Ye.

979
00:35:41,480 --> 00:35:42,680
"Running Wang Erya"!

980
00:35:43,380 --> 00:35:43,900
Now,

981
00:35:44,780 --> 00:35:46,360
you messed up her legs like this.

982
00:35:46,360 --> 00:35:48,090
How is Erya supposed to run now?

983
00:35:48,940 --> 00:35:49,400
Look...

984
00:35:49,840 --> 00:35:50,840
Well, I...

985
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:52,170
I want to use the tape...

986
00:35:52,300 --> 00:35:53,160
Use the tape...

987
00:35:54,460 --> 00:35:55,440
I want to tape it

988
00:35:55,780 --> 00:35:56,500
from the back!

989
00:35:56,500 --> 00:35:58,730
You wouldn't see anything from the front.

990
00:35:58,730 --> 00:36:00,530
It's not about the front or back!

991
00:36:00,710 --> 00:36:02,040
Do you even know who I am?

992
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:04,210
Do you know
how much this painting is worth?

993
00:36:04,210 --> 00:36:06,010
Have you ever walked into a gallery
and seen

994
00:36:06,010 --> 00:36:07,380
a painting held together with tape?

995
00:36:07,380 --> 00:36:09,340
You ruined my painting!

996
00:36:14,420 --> 00:36:14,880
Well...

997
00:36:15,860 --> 00:36:17,320
Look, sir, how about this?

998
00:36:17,510 --> 00:36:18,630
How much is your painting?

999
00:36:18,630 --> 00:36:19,510
I'll pay for it.

1000
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:22,820
Worth a fortune—try and pay that!

1001
00:36:24,530 --> 00:36:25,590
Why are you smiling?

1002
00:36:25,590 --> 00:36:26,520
What's so funny?

1003
00:36:26,980 --> 00:36:27,880
You ruined my painting,

1004
00:36:27,880 --> 00:36:29,110
and now you're insulting me too?

1005
00:36:29,110 --> 00:36:30,440
I... I didn't.

1006
00:36:30,570 --> 00:36:31,230
You didn't?

1007
00:36:31,380 --> 00:36:31,800
No, no...

1008
00:36:31,800 --> 00:36:33,130
Then pay me 80,000 yuan!

1009
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:36,900
Cao.

1010
00:36:37,900 --> 00:36:39,500
That's a bit too much, right?

1011
00:36:43,800 --> 00:36:45,150
Sir, that's

1012
00:36:45,150 --> 00:36:46,420
bordering on extortion, right?

1013
00:36:46,420 --> 00:36:46,960
What?

1014
00:36:47,400 --> 00:36:48,730
What do you mean, "extortion"?

1015
00:36:48,730 --> 00:36:50,170
You ruined the painting,

1016
00:36:50,170 --> 00:36:51,190
and now you're insulting my buddy!

1017
00:36:51,190 --> 00:36:52,440
What do you want?

1018
00:36:52,440 --> 00:36:53,900
Liangliang, Liangliang!

1019
00:36:57,840 --> 00:36:58,460
Brother

1020
00:36:59,300 --> 00:37:01,000
from Yantai,

1021
00:37:01,670 --> 00:37:02,670
every place

1022
00:37:03,190 --> 00:37:05,090
has its rules.

1023
00:37:05,650 --> 00:37:08,340
Without rules, there's no order.

1024
00:37:08,780 --> 00:37:10,550
What we say is the rules!

1025
00:37:10,650 --> 00:37:12,170
The rules are what we say!

1026
00:37:12,210 --> 00:37:13,280
You didn't check what kind of place

1027
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:14,440
Room 108 is first?

1028
00:37:14,440 --> 00:37:14,920
You think

1029
00:37:14,920 --> 00:37:16,320
you can just move in here?

1030
00:37:16,340 --> 00:37:17,440
This is just a hostel!

1031
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:18,360
I rented a bed.

1032
00:37:18,590 --> 00:37:19,840
That makes it mine.

1033
00:37:20,170 --> 00:37:21,050
There was stuff on it,

1034
00:37:21,050 --> 00:37:22,280
so I had to move it!

1035
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:23,150
And I accidentally damaged

1036
00:37:23,150 --> 00:37:24,400
your painting in the process!

1037
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:25,530
I apologized to you.

1038
00:37:25,630 --> 00:37:27,360
And I said I could pay you for it.

1039
00:37:27,530 --> 00:37:28,590
What other rules are there?

1040
00:37:28,590 --> 00:37:29,760
"What other rules?"

1041
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:31,190
If you're a tiger, hide your claws;

1042
00:37:31,190 --> 00:37:32,980
if you're a dragon, keep your head down!

1043
00:37:32,980 --> 00:37:34,130
That's the rule!

1044
00:37:34,190 --> 00:37:35,820
"If you're a tiger, hide your claws."

1045
00:37:35,820 --> 00:37:37,690
Some tiger—really good at backing down.

1046
00:37:37,690 --> 00:37:38,440
What do you mean by that?

1047
00:37:38,440 --> 00:37:39,900
Liangliang, Liangliang!

1048
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:41,450
Back off.

1049
00:37:41,460 --> 00:37:41,880
You...

1050
00:37:45,150 --> 00:37:47,820
Brother from Yantai,

1051
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:51,150
you're being a bit arrogant here.

1052
00:37:51,500 --> 00:37:52,280
Do you know

1053
00:37:52,690 --> 00:37:54,500
what happened to the last guy

1054
00:37:54,510 --> 00:37:56,440
who got cocky with us

1055
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:57,280
in this room?

1056
00:37:57,320 --> 00:37:58,650
He's still on crutches!

1057
00:37:58,670 --> 00:38:01,000
With a urine bag
dangling from one of them!

1058
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:02,480
I see.

1059
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:04,210
Understood.

1060
00:38:05,150 --> 00:38:05,800
Sir, I...

1061
00:38:06,110 --> 00:38:07,510
once again, I apologize.

1062
00:38:07,840 --> 00:38:08,570
I apologize.

1063
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:10,930
Think about how much this painting

1064
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:11,880
is really worth

1065
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:13,170
and name a price.

1066
00:38:13,170 --> 00:38:14,230
I'll pay you for it.

1067
00:38:14,440 --> 00:38:15,570
Rest assured, guys.

1068
00:38:15,860 --> 00:38:16,650
I won't be

1069
00:38:16,940 --> 00:38:18,400
staying in this room long.

1070
00:38:20,010 --> 00:38:20,590
And I won't

1071
00:38:20,590 --> 00:38:21,920
cause you any more trouble.

1072
00:38:21,920 --> 00:38:23,250
I usually go to bed late.

1073
00:38:23,480 --> 00:38:24,670
I'll head out for a walk.

1074
00:38:24,670 --> 00:38:26,000
You guys go to bed first.

1075
00:38:41,630 --> 00:38:43,690
This is a specialty from my hometown.

1076
00:38:44,460 --> 00:38:45,320
Please, try it.

1077
00:38:51,820 --> 00:38:53,480
What, never seen food before?

1078
00:38:55,530 --> 00:38:57,150
This goes great with booze!

1079
00:38:57,400 --> 00:38:59,110
Why were you holding me back?

1080
00:38:59,210 --> 00:39:00,600
I'm furious!

1081
00:39:00,840 --> 00:39:02,040
I want to kick his ass!

1082
00:39:03,510 --> 00:39:04,980
I'm furious!

1083
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:12,920
Have some.

1084
00:39:13,230 --> 00:39:13,840
Calm down.

1085
00:39:14,480 --> 00:39:15,760
Get lost. Now.

1086
00:39:20,890 --> 00:39:25,520
[Seasons Change Hotel]

1087
00:39:25,520 --> 00:39:28,030
[Guest Room]

1088
00:39:30,300 --> 00:39:31,900
Why are you two sitting here?

1089
00:39:31,940 --> 00:39:32,870
Waiting for you.

1090
00:39:33,900 --> 00:39:34,440
Look.

1091
00:39:41,300 --> 00:39:42,530
Do what you have to do.

1092
00:39:46,900 --> 00:39:47,320
Done.

1093
00:39:47,980 --> 00:39:49,090
It's useless.

1094
00:39:49,230 --> 00:39:50,130
How is it useless?

1095
00:39:50,130 --> 00:39:50,630
Watch.

1096
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:53,110
Three, two, one.

1097
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:57,570
See? It didn't work.

1098
00:39:59,170 --> 00:40:00,650
Must be the wrong method.

1099
00:40:01,630 --> 00:40:03,290
What trick should we use then?

1100
00:40:04,880 --> 00:40:05,920
It's no use!

1101
00:40:05,960 --> 00:40:06,460
Look.

1102
00:40:12,170 --> 00:40:13,430
Well, what do we do now?

1103
00:40:13,820 --> 00:40:16,020
No wonder he said we should sleep first.

1104
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:18,900
Can't believe someone
can snore that badly.

1105
00:40:19,440 --> 00:40:20,970
He's an honest man, though.

1106
00:40:21,230 --> 00:40:22,960
What, now you're praising him?

1107
00:40:22,980 --> 00:40:25,130
If there's a problem,
it should be treated.

1108
00:40:25,130 --> 00:40:25,790
Watch this.

1109
00:40:36,190 --> 00:40:36,850
He's awake.

1110
00:40:37,190 --> 00:40:37,630
Man,

1111
00:40:38,380 --> 00:40:39,820
you were snoring!

1112
00:40:40,730 --> 00:40:41,920
Don't fall asleep yet.

1113
00:40:41,920 --> 00:40:43,380
Wait until we're asleep first,

1114
00:40:43,380 --> 00:40:43,900
okay?

1115
00:40:43,900 --> 00:40:45,070
Get up and stay awake for a bit.

1116
00:40:45,070 --> 00:40:46,090
You guys sleep. You guys sleep.

1117
00:40:46,090 --> 00:40:47,020
You sleep first.

1118
00:40:52,440 --> 00:40:53,500
He's out that fast?

1119
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:54,860
Make him sit up!

1120
00:40:55,570 --> 00:40:57,760
Lift him. One, two, three. Up you go.

1121
00:40:59,880 --> 00:41:01,110
Don't fall asleep yet!

1122
00:41:01,110 --> 00:41:01,840
Wake up a bit!

1123
00:41:02,380 --> 00:41:03,590
You two go to sleep.

1124
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:05,620
I'll handle things here.

1125
00:41:06,130 --> 00:41:07,130
Let's have a chat.

1126
00:41:07,820 --> 00:41:08,300
Sorry.

1127
00:41:09,110 --> 00:41:09,710
It's okay.

1128
00:41:10,170 --> 00:41:10,940
It's just...

1129
00:41:11,670 --> 00:41:12,240
If you...

1130
00:41:57,280 --> 00:41:57,980
Mr. Tao,

1131
00:41:57,980 --> 00:41:59,500
I thought it was an earthquake.

1132
00:41:59,500 --> 00:42:00,550
If you smash my glass top,

1133
00:42:00,550 --> 00:42:01,030
it'll break,

1134
00:42:01,030 --> 00:42:02,090
and you'll get cut.

1135
00:42:02,300 --> 00:42:03,730
What? What brings you here...

1136
00:42:03,730 --> 00:42:04,460
at this hour?

1137
00:42:04,500 --> 00:42:06,430
Can you kick that guy out of my room?

1138
00:42:06,650 --> 00:42:07,580
He offended you?

1139
00:42:08,570 --> 00:42:09,460
He snores.

1140
00:42:10,420 --> 00:42:11,220
I can't sleep.

1141
00:42:11,530 --> 00:42:13,330
Not just me. None of us can sleep.

1142
00:42:13,530 --> 00:42:14,900
If he snores, just whistle.

1143
00:42:14,900 --> 00:42:16,210
Whistle, my foot.

1144
00:42:16,210 --> 00:42:17,410
I play the saxophone.

1145
00:42:17,690 --> 00:42:18,980
But we can't kick someone out

1146
00:42:18,980 --> 00:42:19,880
just for snoring.

1147
00:42:19,880 --> 00:42:21,400
Who doesn't snore when they sleep?

1148
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:22,000
This is...

1149
00:42:22,070 --> 00:42:23,600
Will you kick him out or not?

1150
00:42:24,280 --> 00:42:25,940
You're putting me on the spot.

1151
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:27,360
Didn't you say you were tight on cash?

1152
00:42:27,360 --> 00:42:28,560
A friend gave it to me.

1153
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:31,210
Even so, I still need an excuse

1154
00:42:31,210 --> 00:42:31,650
to kick him out.

1155
00:42:31,650 --> 00:42:33,000
Just say a new guest arrived

1156
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:34,070
and move him to a new room.

1157
00:42:34,070 --> 00:42:34,710
Get him out of our room.

1158
00:42:34,710 --> 00:42:35,820
What if I say that and he won't move?

1159
00:42:35,820 --> 00:42:36,610
Give him some attitude!

1160
00:42:36,610 --> 00:42:37,380
I don't have the nerve for that.

1161
00:42:37,380 --> 00:42:38,820
My attitude wouldn't scare anyone.

1162
00:42:38,820 --> 00:42:40,350
Are you going to do it or not?

1163
00:42:41,300 --> 00:42:43,190
Could you give me just a moment to think?

1164
00:42:43,190 --> 00:42:44,860
No need to think—just do it.

1165
00:42:45,860 --> 00:42:47,030
You took it, so now you have to deliver.
